NX-OS 10.4(2) patch upgrade to 10.5(4)M to remediate critical CVEs impacting BIOS and diagnostics


This change request covers patch management for Cisco Nexus devices currently running NX-OS 10.4(2). Four CVEs were identified; two are relevant to our environment:
CVE-2024-20397 – NX-OS Image Verification Bypass (BIOS impact)
CVE-2025-20111 – Health Monitoring Diagnostics DoS (workaround available) The other two CVEs (IS-IS and DHCPv6 SISF) are not applicable as those features are disabled. The upgrade to NX-OS 10.5(4)M ensures compliance, mitigates risks, and maintains rollback readiness.
Main Agenda:
Perform NX-OS patch upgrade to 10.4(5)M
Remediate BIOS vulnerability (CVE-2024-20397)
Mitigate diagnostics DoS vulnerability (CVE-2025-20111)
Confirm unaffected CVEs are not relevant
Validate upgrade success and rollback plan
